  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">We extend recent results on scalar–tensor theories to the case of an <math altimg="si1.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mi>O</mi><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>N</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></math> -invariant multiplet. Some exact fixed point solutions of the RG flow equations are discussed. We find that also in the functional context, on employing a standard “type-I” cutoff, too many scalars destroy the gravitational fixed point. For <math altimg="si2.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mi>d</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn></math> we show the existence of the gravitationally dressed Wilson–Fisher fixed point also for <math altimg="si3.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mi>N</mi><mo>></mo><mn>1</mn></math> . We discuss also the results of the analysis for a different, scalar-free, coarse-graining scheme.</subfield>
